Task 3.3: Integrate Add/Remove with HabitStore

Summary: Added addHabit() and removeHabit() methods to ConfigurationViewModel that delegate to HabitStore and reload the habits array. addHabit() enforces the 4-slot limit via canAddSlot guard. Wired the '+ SLOT' button in ConfigurationView to present AddSlotSheet via .sheet(isPresented:), passing the save callback through to viewModel.addHabit().

Files modified:
- ductiva/ConfigurationViewModel.swift — Added addHabit(), removeHabit() methods
- ductiva/ConfigurationView.swift — Added showAddSlotSheet state, .sheet() for AddSlotSheet, wired button action
- ductivaTests/ConfigurationViewModelTests.swift — Added 5 tests: addHabitPersists, removeHabitDeletes, addBlockedAtMaxSlots, addHabitUpdatesSlotCounter, removeHabitUpdatesCanAddSlot

Why: Core CRUD workflow — users need to add/remove habit slots from the configuration screen.
